description.narrative: Reduce the transmission and impact of HIV/AIDS through support for prevention, care and treatment programs.

This award strives to reduce the transmission and impact of HIVAIDS through support for prevention, care and treatment programs. More specifically, this includes PR5446713-M001-Funding VAT law change-SGE500-15-F-0125, M002[Includes all services classified under subobject 2511 that are for government-owned and long-term leased buildings rather than short-term leased buildings.]. description.narrative: Strong partners for over five decades, Tanzania and the United States are working towards a shared vision of improving the quality of life for all Tanzanians. Despite its political stability and high levels of economic growth over the past two decades, roughly 28 percent of the population lives below the poverty line. The goal of U.S. assistance is to promote a healthy, prosperous, democratic, well-governed and secure Tanzania.
